model_response.text: To start a startup in San Francisco, you should aim to create an environment where startups are the "cool thing to do" and encourage people with relevant expertise to collaborate and interact. Focus on building a community of people who are passionate about startups and willing to work together to help one another. Additionally, the best way to attract clients is to understand the needs of the market and provide a unique selling proposition. Focus on server-based software, and consider using a high-level language like Lisp to write software quickly and efficiently.
